        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(feishu): add pagination support for drive list and info",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nFeishu drive list/info missing pagination support\n\n## Changes\n\n- `extensions/feishu/src/drive-schema.ts`: Add page_size, page_token, and all parameters\n- `extensions/feishu/src/drive.ts`: Add pagination loop for listFolder and getFileInfo\n- `extensions/feishu/src/drive.test.ts`: Add regression tests for list.all pagination\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: Feishu drive list and info actions lacked pagination, failing when folders contain more than 10 items (the default page size).\n\nReal environment tested: ubuntu-24.04, Node 24, branch fix/issue-93928-feishu-drive-pagination.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch:\n\n```bash\nnode scripts/test-projects.mjs extensions/feishu/src/drive.test.ts\n```\n\nEvidence after fix:\n\n```text\n$ node scripts/test-projects.mjs extensions/feishu/src/drive.test.ts\n RUN  v4.1.8\n\n ✓ 19 tests passed (19)\n\n Including:\n ✓ forwards list pagination cursors and returns continuation metadata\n ✓ searches subsequent drive pages for info while preserving folder scope\n ✓ list with all:true paginates through multiple pages\n ✓ list without all:true does not paginate when has_more is true\n```\n\nObserved result after fix: All 19 drive tests pass. Pagination behavior verified: `all: true` loops through pages via has_more + page_token; default (no `all`) returns single page.\n\nWhat was not tested: End-to-end with a real Feishu tenant with >10 items in a folder (requires platform-specific credentials).\n\nCloses: #93928",
        "branch": "fix/issue-93928-feishu-drive-pagination",
